interventionNames: Drug: 20 mg/120 mg artemether-lumefantrine (AL) + 20 mg ruxolitinib phosphate (Rux)

pred_item.label: Artemether-lumefantrine + Ruxolitinib
pred_item.description: Participants received standard artemether-lumefantrine orally twice daily for 3 days. Ruxolitinib (20 mg) was administered orally 2 hours after artemether-lumefantrine twice daily for 3 days.

pred_item.label: Artemether-lumefantrine + Placebo
pred_item.description: Participants received standard artemether-lumefantrine orally twice daily for 3 days. Placebo was administered orally 2 hours after artemether-lumefantrine twice daily for 3 days.

ref_item.name: 20 mg/120 mg artemether-lumefantrine (AL) + 20 mg ruxolitinib phosphate (Rux)
ref_item.description: Rux administered 2 hours after AL administration, twice daily (b.i.d) for 3 consecutive days (6 doses in total).

pred_item.name: Ruxolitinib
pred_item.description: 20 mg (Jakavi; Incyte) administered orally 2 hours after artemether-lumefantrine twice daily for 3 days (total dose 120 mg).

ref_item.name: 20 mg/120 mg artemether-lumefantrine (AL) + Placebo
ref_item.description: Placebo administered 2 hours after AL administration, twice daily (b.i.d) for 3 consecutive days (6 doses in total).

pred_item.name: Placebo
pred_item.description: Placebo administered orally 2 hours after artemether-lumefantrine twice daily for 3 days.

ref_item.measure: Number of Participant With Treatment-Related Adverse Events as Assessed by CTCAE V4.03, All of Observed and Self-reported AEs Affected, by Treatment Regimen.
ref_item.description: Incidence, severity and relationship of observed and self-reported adverse events (AEs) were reported during the study up to 28 days after AL+Rux and AL+Placebo administration in all participants by treatment regimens.
ref_item.timeFrame: up to 28 days after AL+Rux and AL+placebo administration

pred_item.measure: Frequency of adverse events and serious adverse events

ref_item.measure: Number of Participants With Changes of Systolic and Diastolic Blood Pressure

pred_item.measure: Clinically significant changes in physical examination
pred_item.timeFrame: Through study completion, up to Day 29

ref_item.measure: Number of Participants With Changes in Heart Rate

pred_item.description: Assessment of the effect of ruxolitinib in combination with artemether-lumefantrine on the inhibition of phosphorylation of signal transducer and activator of transcription 3 (pSTAT3) compared to placebo.
pred_item.timeFrame: Predose and up to 168 hours relative to first artemether-lumefantrine dose
